article.description: — Terry Taylor scored 18 points and pulled down 10 rebounds as Austin Peay defeated Tennessee State 71-56 on Saturday.
article.headline: Taylor lifts Austin Peay over Tennessee State 71-56
article.linkText: Taylor lifts Austin Peay over Tennessee State 71-56
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- — Terry Taylor scored 18 points and pulled down 10 rebounds as Austin Peay defeated Tennessee State 71-56 on Saturday. Jordyn Adams added 15 points and seven rebounds for Austin Peay (9-6, 5-4 Ohio Valley Conference). Alec Woodard and Carlos Paez each had 10 points. Austin Peay dominated the first half and led 42-16 at halftime. Ravel Moody and Mark Freeman each scored 16 points for the Tigers (3-12, 2-10). Amorey Womack had 12 points. Austin Peay defeated Tennessee State 68-59 on Dec. 30 and sweeps the season series. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
